<L>__{interior privy chamber, whitehall palace night}
<A>__{now elizabeth is with raleigh again, listening as he goes on speaking to her, now directly.}
<C>__{raleigh}
<D>__{pure naked fragile hope, when all your senses scream at you, lost! lost! imagine it. day after day, staring west, the rising sun on your back, the setting sun in your eyes, hoping, hoping }
<A>__{sir christopher hatton enters.}
<C>__{hatton}
<D>__{majesty, the archduke and the court are waiting.}
<C>__{elizabeth}
<P>__{(sharply)}
<D>__{let them wait!}
<P>__{(to raleigh)}
<D>__{go on, mr raleigh. you were hoping.}
<A>__{hatton bows and leaves, frowning.}
<C>__{raleigh}
<D>__{at first it's no more than a haze on the horizon, the ghost of a haze, the pure line corrupted. but clouds do that, and storms. so you watch, you watch.}
